                  </persName>
            , a pawnbroker, in St. John-street. The prisoner pawned this gown on Saturday morning, between seven and eight o'clock, for 4 s. I am sure of him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I found it on the back galley stairs, wrapped in brown paper. I enquired, but could hear of nobody losing one, and being pressed for rent, I pawned it.</p>
